{
  "description": "A low-angle, close-up photograph showcases a vibrant red tulip in full bloom against a clear, bright blue sky. The tulip is the dominant element, filling much of the frame. Its petals are a rich, deep red, transitioning to a warm yellow-orange towards the center where the reproductive parts are visible. The inner petals reveal a touch of green, creating a beautiful contrast. The stem is a slender green stalk, partially obscured by the angle. A second tulip, out of focus and partially visible, appears on the left edge of the image. The lighting is natural and highlights the texture of the petals. The background is a smooth, untextured blue.",
